  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this project is to investigate the subjective and clinical outcome in
      patients at least one year after DIP arthroplasty and compare them to matched patients with
      an arthrodesis.

      The primary endpoint is the satisfaction with the treatment result of in the
      motion-preserving DIP surgery at follow-up.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
